info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued November 16 at 1:13AM EST until November 16 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Key West
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 AM EST EARLY THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues. * WHERE...A portion of Florida, including the following county, Upper Keys in Monroe County. * WHEN...Until 330 AM EST. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 113 AM EST, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the warned area. Between 8 and 14 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 2 to 4 inches are possible in the warned area. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Key Largo, Jewfish Creek Bridge, East End Of Channel 5 Bridge, Plantation, Rock Harbor, Windley Key, Route 1/card Sound, Route 1/card Sound Road Split, Upper Matecumbe Key and Teatable Key. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Do not drive your vehicle into areas where the water covers the roadway. The water depth may be too great to allow your car to cross safely.
